---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Roth Conversion Calculator: Optimize Your Tax Bracket Strategy",
  "description": "Calculate the optimal amount to convert from a Traditional IRA to a Roth IRA based on your current and future tax brackets.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "FireMaths"
  },
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is a Roth Conversion?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A Roth conversion is the process of moving funds from a traditional IRA or 401(k) to a Roth IRA. You pay taxes on the converted amount now, but future growth and withdrawals are tax-free."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When should I do a Roth Conversion?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The best time to do a Roth conversion is during early retirement or other low-income years when your marginal tax rate is significantly lower than what you expect it to be in the future (e.g., when RMDs begin)."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is there a penalty for a Roth Conversion?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No, there is no early withdrawal penalty for a Roth conversion itself. However, you must wait 5 years before withdrawing the converted principal penalty-free if you are under 59.5."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
};

export const meta = {
  title: "Roth Conversion Calculator",
  description: "Calculate the optimal amount to convert from a Traditional IRA to a Roth IRA.",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="firemaths"
  title="Roth Conversion Calculator"
  description="Calculate the optimal amount to convert from a Traditional IRA to a Roth IRA."
  canonical="https://firemaths.info/roth-conversion-calculator"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Roth Conversion Calculator</h1>
      <p>Find the sweet spot for your annual Roth conversions.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>Conversion Optimizer</h2>
      <p>This tool helps you estimate the optimal amount to convert to a Roth IRA to fill up a specific tax bracket without spilling into the next one.</p>

      <div class="calculator-form">
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="currentIncome">Current Taxable Income (Before Conversion)</label>
          <div class="input-prefix">
            <span>$</span>
            <input type="number" id="currentIncome" value="40000" min="0" step="1000" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="targetBracket">Target Tax Bracket to Fill (Single Filer - 2024)</label>
          <select id="targetBracket">
            <option value="11600">10% Bracket (Up to $11,600)</option>
            <option value="47150" selected>12% Bracket (Up to $47,150)</option>
            <option value="100525">22% Bracket (Up to $100,525)</option>
            <option value="191950">24% Bracket (Up to $191,950)</option>
            <option value="243725">32% Bracket (Up to $243,725)</option>
          </select>
        </div>

        <button id="calcBtn" class="calc-btn">Calculate Conversion Room</button>
      </div>

      <div class="results" id="results" style="display:none;">
        <h3>Optimal Conversion Amount: <span id="conversionAmount" style="color:var(--accent-color)">$0</span></h3>
        <p>By converting this amount, you maximize the <span id="bracketPercent">12%</span> bracket without your income spilling over into the higher bracket. <em>Note: This is a simplified estimate for a single filer using standard brackets and does not include standard deduction impacts. Consult a tax professional.</em></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card content-section">
      <h2>How Roth Conversions Work</h2>
      <p>A Roth conversion involves taking money from a pre-tax account (like a Traditional IRA) and moving it to an after-tax account (Roth IRA). You pay ordinary income tax on the amount converted in the year you do it.</p>
      <p>This strategy is highly effective as part of an overall <a href="/tax-optimization-fire-guide">Tax Optimization FIRE strategy</a>. By converting funds during low-income years (like early retirement), you lock in a low tax rate and allow the money to grow tax-free forever.</p>

      <h3>The Roth Conversion Ladder</h3>
      <p>For early retirees, the Roth Conversion Ladder is a vital strategy. You convert a specific amount each year. After five years, that converted "principal" can be withdrawn penalty-free, even if you are under 59.5. This provides a steady stream of tax-free income.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.getElementById('calcBtn').addEventListener('click', function() {
      const currentIncome = parseFloat(document.getElementById('currentIncome').value) || 0;
      const targetBracketLimit = parseFloat(document.getElementById('targetBracket').value) || 0;

      const selectEl = document.getElementById('targetBracket');
      const bracketText = selectEl.options[selectEl.selectedIndex].text.split(' ')[0];

      let conversionRoom = targetBracketLimit - currentIncome;
      if (conversionRoom < 0) conversionRoom = 0;

      document.getElementById('conversionAmount').innerText = '$' + conversionRoom.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 0, maximumFractionDigits: 0});
      document.getElementById('bracketPercent').innerText = bracketText;

      document.getElementById('results').style.display = 'block';
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }
    .hero {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
    }
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .hero p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .card {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
    }
    .calculator-form {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .input-group {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .input-prefix {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 6px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .input-prefix span {
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .input-prefix input, select {
      flex: 1;
      padding: 0.5rem;
      border: none;
      background: transparent;
      color: inherit;
      font-size: 1rem;
      outline: none;
    }
    select {
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 6px;
      background: #111;
      padding: 0.6rem;
    }
    .calc-btn {
      background: var(--accent-color);
      color: #000;
      border: none;
      padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-weight: bold;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-size: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      transition: opacity 0.2s;
    }
    .calc-btn:hover {
      opacity: 0.9;
    }
    .results {
      padding-top: 1rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    }
    .content-section h2, .content-section h3 {
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }
    .content-section p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    a {
      color: var(--accent-color);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
